# Virtual Analyst — Investment Analytics Platform

## Tech Stack
- Backend: Python 3.11+, FastAPI (async), PostgreSQL (Supabase), Redis (async)
- Frontend: TypeScript (51+ pages)
- Shared Engine: shared/fm_shared/ (valuation, monte_carlo, statements, sensitivity)
- API: apps/api/app/ (routers, middleware, services)
- LLM: Task-label-based routing with configurable model/temperature per label
- DTF: tools/dtf/ (developer-only calibration and validation CLI)

## Active Workstreams
1. Platform Remediation: 23 items (REM-01 to REM-23), 6 sprints
2. PIM Module: Sentiment-augmented portfolio intelligence, 7 phases, 9 DB tables
3. DTF Framework: Parameter calibration + ongoing prediction validation

## Key Modules
- AFS (Annual Financial Statements): apps/api/app/routers/afs.py (2500+ lines — being refactored)
- Budgets: apps/api/app/routers/budgets.py (1400+ lines — being split)
- Valuation: shared/fm_shared/analysis/valuation.py (DCF)
- Monte Carlo: shared/fm_shared/analysis/monte_carlo.py
- Statements: shared/fm_shared/model/statements.py
- Auth: apps/api/app/middleware/auth.py

## Sub-agents available in .claude/agents/
- platform-remediator: Fix REM-XX backlog items
- security-auditor: Read-only security review
- financial-engine: Shared financial model engine work
- pim-architect: PIM module architecture and design
- pim-builder: PIM module implementation
- dtf-engineer: Developer Testing Framework
- frontend-builder: TypeScript frontend pages
- financial-reviewer: Read-only financial/statistical validation

## Critical Rules
- Sprint 1 remediation MUST complete before any PIM code
- All async handlers: no synchronous blocking calls
- All SQL: parameterised queries or ORM, never f-strings
- All financial calcs: reference CFA/IAS/ISA standard in docstrings
- PIM endpoints: check_pim_access(tenant_id) as first operation
- DTF: never expose on public API
- Statistical tests: deterministic, then LLM for narrative only
